description: Temporarily disconnect both external output cables from the PSU circuit (isolate the battery, its internal series resistor, and the PSU green LED). Then use one external cable pair (or clip leads) to connect directly across the battery terminals, bypassing the PSU’s internal wiring, and briefly power a known‑good LED+resistor or lamp. Observe whether that external load lights. This checks whether the battery itself can source current under load, distinguishing a dead/very high‑impedance battery from a downstream wiring/open‑circuit problem., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module (battery only, external load test),
description: Disconnect both PSU output cables from the internal PCB so that only the battery terminals are accessible. Using clip leads or two of the loose fast-connection cables, connect a known‑good 12 V‑rated test load (e.g., a spare LED+series resistor or one control‑module indicator branch) directly across the battery terminals, bypassing all PSU internal wiring and LEDs. Insert the battery and observe whether the external test load lights or shows any sign of current. This isolates and tests the battery’s ability to supply current under load., outcome='The multimeter current measurement could not be performed because the tool is unavailable. The PSU Status LED (green) was visually inspected and is currently lit, with no observable internal fault.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module (battery under load, using series chain as test load),
description: With all control modules and the load module reconnected in their correct order and all switches ON, leave the PSU exactly as in normal operation. Remove and then re‑insert the 12 V battery while watching carefully: (1) whether any control‑module LED or the load indicator lamp flickers even very briefly, and (2) whether there is any tiny spark or sound at the battery contacts when inserting it. This uses the whole downstream chain as a load and checks whether the battery/PSU can actually source current (any flicker/spark) or is effectively open/high‑impedance despite its own green LED lighting., outcome='The PSU Status LED (green) is lit, and the internal indicator lamp in the load cube is not lit. All eight control‑module green LEDs are physically absent and cannot be observed.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=125.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
